args: *pant* *huff* Looks like I managed to\nshake 'em off my tail.
So this was my parents' lab, eh? Well,\ntheir recipes must be here somewhere.\nTime for a good old-fashioned ransack!
...Interesting. I think I've put most of it\ntogether at this point.

Their work on the omega key
was never completed, but it gave
rise to new discoveries that were
later adopted by the military.
That weapon Logius said was used in town\nmust be one of them...
But the military would definitely have all\nthat stuff under heavy lock and key,\nwhich meeeans...
Well, whatever the case, I won't forgive\nanyone who uses alchemy to hurt people—\nespecially not with my parents' research!
The fact you would come here is almost\ntoo absurd to believe. Yet here you stand.
But this won't do. No, it won't do at all.\nYou were meant to await judgment in\nyour cell like a good little criminal.
I'm no criminal! That attack was an\ninside job perpetrated by the military!
And just what have you found here, mmm?
These notes show my parents' research\ninto the omega key, as well as how the\narmy adapted it for military use.
And if the same methods described here\nwere utilized in the attack...
Then it is likely the perpetrator was a\nmilitary member with access to this lab.\nI admit, there is logic to it.
By way of rebuttal, I would ask you:\nWhat of it?
Are you dense? I'm saying you should be\ninvestigating your OWN people instead of\ncoming after somebody like me!
Oh, I see little need to investigate;\nthe perpetrator you speak of was myself.
Augus asked me to bring you in.\nI needed a pretext. Your actual guilt\nin the matter is entirely beside the point.
So you're gonna frame me for a crime\nYOU committed?!
I found a most delightful toy in here and\nsimply couldn't resist performing a little\nexperiment. Surely you've felt that urge?
I've told you before, I'll never use alchemy\nto hurt people. Don't lump me in with a\nmonster like you!
Then what does that make your parents?
They would never have knowingly\nlet their work hurt anyo—
NOW who is dense?! You have seen the\nrecords here; it's obvious they adapted\ntheir research for military use themselves!
They knew full well they were making\ntools of murder, yet they continued their\nresearch all the same.
That can't be true! They meant for the\nomega key to help people!
You don't even know their faces, yet you\nare so certain you know their hearts?
I know enough to know they never would\nhave gone along with a big loser like you!\nAnd neither will I, you...you RAT FINK!
Oh dear, that won't do.\nNo, it won't do at all.
You know something? Augus asked me to\nbring you in alive, but I think I am going\nto kill you here and now instead.
I'll simply have to tell him you were a\nnaughty thing who resisted arrest,\nleaving me with no choice.
I have been waiting for the chance to\nspring you ever since they brought you in.
But then you went and broke yourself out,\nbecause of course you did. Do you have\nANY idea how hard you are to track?
I know, I know. I'm a terrible daughter.\nSo then! Any chance you thought up a\ngenius plan to escape on your way here?
No plans, but I DID bring a few of your\nlittle craft projects along.
That's my mom! Those should be plenty!
Are you morons enjoying\nlistening to them chat?\nKILL THEM ALREADY!
Hey, any of you guys got kids? I'm told\nthese are all the rage with the young'uns!
Time to make like a banana and split!
Damn you, girl! You won't escape.\nMark my words, I WILL hunt you down!
Well, I'm not sticking around and find out.\nThey'll have sent soldiers to the house,\nand if they're going to keep chasing us...
We have to leave, Ilia. We have to go far\nenough that they can't follow—to a place\nwhere no one will know who we are.
Aw, are you asking me to elope?
How can you joke at a time like this?!
Just how I'm wired, I guess. Sorry.\nBut look, I can't leave. I've got something\nI need to finish up here.
Does it have to do with your parents?
Yeah, I may have purloined all of their\nomega key research back at the lab.
I have to know what was driving them to\ndo this work, which means I need—
Enough. I know better than to try and\nchange your mind once it's set.
*sigh* I really do spoil her.\nBut if this is what she wants...
